/span><hr size=1> There was a patch??? <p><font face="Blackchancery" color="#4682b4" size=+2>Carabella Valenteen</font><p>"The bonds of friendship are forged in laughter, but cemented in tears"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujamisiashido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jamisia Shido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/6/02 6:34:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Slow-motion animations.</span><hr size=1> Not so much a patch as an updated file. They were tweaking with the texture &amp; lighting effects for performance with the videocards that support that feature-set.<br><br>It just happened to have a rather nasty side-effect, as most of the patches regretably do. I don't feel guilty for pointing out their faults, just because they've made a string of reasonable changes to the game. (The same changes half of us were asking them to make for three or more years now.) I tell it like it is. The fact of the matter is, most of their patches require a second patch to fix the first patch, if not a number of subsequent fixes taking place over months. It's not unheard of for EverQuest, and I can vouchsafe that as a player who's experienced them.<br><br>And yes, there was a surprisingly quick (in Verant terms) replacement put up on the patcher a few hours later.<br><br>For the trolls (and I don't mean the ones from Grobb) -- I have fun playing the game, I just think the company and designers are pinheads. I don't call them names lightly (nor belligerently). It's taken quite a few years for me to develop that quirk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usllackblader.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sllack Blader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/6/02 1:55:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Slow-motion animations.</span><hr size=1> Cool, I want to see this. Is it just Luclin mobs? <p><b>The Kane Bayle Community is at: <a href="http://www.kanebayle.com">kanebayle.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2152.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.threadControl?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2152.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2152.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" c